ymt888
Petaling Jaya, Malaysia
1422604
Reviewed June 6, 2018
Recommended by tour guide
Apparently this is the best banh xeo in town. Once arrived we were shown to a table and once seated there is no menu, they will just bring the food for the amount of people they see seated. There is some vegetables, some sort of oily pancake with shrimps, pork skewers, sauce, chili, rice paper. All you have to do is to wrap all the stuff yourselves and stuff it into your mouth. If you need to top anything up, just request more. Then they will come to the table to check the empty plates and charge accordingly. Simple, no nonsense and straightforward. Apart from me finding it a tad oily, the meal was delicious.
Date of visit: March 2018
Ask ymt888 about Banh xeo Ba Duong
Thank ymt888
Lawteckree
Penang Island, Malaysia
5545
Reviewed June 5, 2018
Worth a visit
Decided to give this place a try. Not straight forward to find but most cab drivers would know this place. Once you take a seat, you will be immediately be served with their signature banh xeo. No doubt, it was delicious. The sauce was the highlight of the dish. One serving is enough for 2-3 people. The price is affordable too. A must visit if you visit Da Nang
