Nad1462
Frankfurt, Germany
4121
Reviewed May 15, 2018
A must go to
I discovered the dish while in the south of Vietnam and really wanted to eat it again. Thanks to TripAdvisor we ended up at this place. And boy o boy, it’s gooood. The alley to get to it is a little shady but not dangerous at all. You sit down and get your food. There was no menu as they only serve that one dish. I loved the freshness of the greens and it tasted so good. I’ve been trying different Vietnamese restaurants while travelling in the UK and Europe since and none compares to this little hidden gem.
Date of visit: November 2017
