Mymy P
1
He touched the cat!!!!
Worst experience of our lives! We were looking forward to coming here with alot of advisers telling us its a must go restaurant.
We walked in to a full house, but the further we went in filthier it got. There was rubbish all over the floor, kittens running around. Food scraps from previous diners being reused. Staff were unattentive and almost ignored everything we said to them.
To top if off, looking into the kitchen the staff picked her nose as she continued to prepare the food.
What topped it off was that a waiter grabbed the nem sticks from the table.. as he walked back into the kitchen with them waving around in his hand.. he stopped...
My mind was going crazy telling him “do not touch the cat... do not touch the cat.!!”...and then.. “he touched the cat!!!! And picked it up!!”
#chopstickdrop
Ask Mymy P about Banh xeo Ba Duong
Thank Mymy P
RoamingAway
Honolulu, Hawaii
473
Reviewed April 29, 2018
Amazing food, but a bit smoky in here
Food was amazing. Menu has a few selection but this is a specialty restaurant.
We walked through a narrow alleyway with speeding motorbikes alongside mom-and-pop shops to find the restaurant at the end.
We recommend trying everything including the satay beef which was the most expensive item on the menu. Although the beef was on the drier side, it was still good.
Date of visit: April 2018
